"Imagining horchata as a beer is difficult and set the beer up to be either disgusting or surprisingly good.  For me, this fell on the good side. Drank from a bottle.  It had an almost overwhelming and surprisingly pleasant cinnamon smell. It actually got the core taste of horchata without being undrinkable due to sweetness.  Very smooth and easy to drink. Light carbonation and a very light tongue feel.  The traditional wheat taste was not strong, but enough to balance the sweetness.  As a desert beer, it is pretty good.  I got it out of curiosity and had low expectations for it.  Even though I expected it to be a cavity ""beer", it fulfilled the titular taste without being too sweet."
